examples.en: It consists with the facts.
The payment consists in food.
The club consists of some 40 members.
Real property consists of land and buildings.
A cricket team consists of eleven players.
The work consists mainly of mere wind and splutter.
The ridge consists entirely of volcanic rock.
Freedom consists in the absence of oppressive laws.
Lamb marking consists of three different operations.
The system consists of a motor and a small computer.
The work consists chiefly of interviewing the public.
The exterior of the tooth consists of very hard enamel.
The course consists of 64 lessons organised into 16 units.
The beauty of this picture consists in its balance of colours.
Of late years the wicket consists of three stumps and two bails.
That account consists with the information in the other reports.
The armadillo's armor consists of a series of small, bony plates.
Religion consists in submission and resignation to the divine will.
The piece rate consists of a basic rate and a percentage "plussage".
A gun detachment consists of one non-commissioned officer and nine gunners.
Our video collection consists chiefly of comedies, but we have a few horror movies.
The phrasal verb look up consists of the verb look and the adverbial particle up.
